member_experience_collection.title: Technical Lead
member_experience_collection.description: Panorama acquired Class Companion in March, 2025 where I'm now continuing to pursue Class Companion's mission at a larger scale.

member_experience_collection.title: Co-Founder
member_experience_collection.description:
Class Companion was acquired by Panorama Education in March, 2025.

Focused primarily on product and engineering to give K-12 teachers AI superpowers. Class Companion delivers instant feedback and coaching on assignments to students, using AI. This saves teachers 10+ hours a week spent grading and enables them to spend more time with the students that need additional help.

member_experience_collection.title: Co-Founder
member_experience_collection.description:
Kopa was acquired by Baker Street in 2023.

Kopa was the marketplace for medium-term housing. Moving to a new place is difficult and lonely. Kopa enabled people to browse furnished rentals, find housemates with similar interests and lifestyles, choose beds, and split deposit and rent payments. We believe that exploration and community make people whole. Kopa existed to inspire people to get out of their comfort zones, to form lasting relationships, and to live fuller lives.

Accomplishments:
- Accepted into Y Combinator (1.5% acceptance rate)
- Raised $1m
- Helped 1,000 people (and counting) easily find and rent a home
- Gathered over 5,000 hosts onto the marketplace
- Processed over $5m in rent

member_experience_collection.title: Sr. Technical Consultant
member_experience_collection.description:
Salesforce acquired Sequence in February, 2017, so just like that I was a part of Salesforce Customer Success Group. I worked with clients to lead development teams, building systems that use different tech stacks.

Accomplishments:
- Built the frontend of a cutting-edge blockchain student achievements platform for the largest US university
- Built an AR mobile app prototype that Marc Benioff presented to one of the largest US pharmacy retailers

member_experience_collection.title: Full Stack Engineer
member_experience_collection.description:
I started my full-time career focusing on front-end engineering at Sequence. This position allowed me to take on a variety of responsibilities, while offering the flexibility to work on side projects.

Accomplishments:
- Helped create a CRM for Chipotle employees to build and manage customers, marketing pages, and more
- Built a web app game for Chipotle's marketing team
- Built a website for Opus One featuring scroll-based transitions and animations

member_experience_collection.title: Front End Engineer
member_experience_collection.description:
I worked on the Nest Developers portal that helps developers work with the Nest API and submit products to the Works With Nest Store.

Accomplishments:
- Built the frontend for the Nest Developers portal
- Increased testing code-coverage from ~20% to ~80%

member_experience_collection.title: UI Software Engineer
member_experience_collection.description:
I was in charge of researching, designing, and building two internal applications. Both saved employees hours of their week totaling over $50k saved in annual expenses for the company. The full process involved requirements analysis for both tools, design, development, and iteration/improvement based on employee feedback.

Accomplishments:
- Built a database configuration tool that enabled engineers to view all database keys used on Zazzle.com, search for specific ones, and add/edit/delete specific key values.
- Built a translation tool that allowed the translation team to view untranslated strings based on a set of filters, export them to Excel, import translated strings, and view translated strings based on a set of filters.
- Presented both tools to the entire company at the end of the internship
- Won Pi Day (recited 30 digits of Pi from memory)

member_experience_collection.title: Software Engineer
member_experience_collection.description:
I was incredibly fortunate to be a part of such a well-run agile development team. I was a software engineer, focused on frontend, for the Pulse team, working on online Fifa Ultimate Team content.

Accomplishments:
- One of six agile team members building the first accompanying web app to EA's most profitable game (FIFA)
- Created the entire frontend from scratch with a teammate
- Improved code-coverage (testing) from ~40% to ~95%
- Made it into the credits of FIFA 15!

member_experience_collection.title: Project Manager
member_experience_collection.description:
Jumping into the world of project management taught me a lot in a short amount of time, from dealing with the politics to tight deadlines. Having experience in both software development and project management has given me a valuable outlook on running a functional and cohesive company.

Accomplishments:
- Saved the company $25k/year by coding multiple Pearl scripts and VB Excel macros to automate control room scheduling (the room responsible for powering all of BC and some of Alberta, Washington, Oregon, and California)
- Created 10-year strategic roadmap for Grid Operations team
- Introduced the company to Prezi 3D presentation software for more effective presentations

member_experience_collection.title: Web Developer
member_experience_collection.description:
Diving into the tech capitol of the world was a phenomenal experience, both inside and outside of work. During this internship I truly fell in love with programming and knew that I wanted to pursue frontend engineering. Fun fact: I put VIM keyboard shortcuts poster next to my desk to become a pro VIM-user.

Accomplishments:
- Increased company revenue 17% by creating an application to organize company products, create social posts/press releases, and view analytics
- Learned proper agile development and programming best practices
- Learned about the hardware Gumstix sold (customizable motherboards)

member_experience_collection.title: Co-Founder
member_experience_collection.description:
My classmate and I started a music recommendation system built around Spotify's Discover Weekly concept years before Discover Weekly was released. We were amongst 15 companies accepted into the University of Waterloo's Enterprise Co-op program. We ultimately didn't stick with the project since school and internships stole our attention.

Accomplishments:
- Learned the fundamentals of programming (with help from my co-founder's father who worked at Microsoft)
- Learned the fundamentals of the web, including HTTP, client/server, HTML/CSS, etc.
- Applied software engineering course knowledge to a real-world application
- Released an Alpha version of the web app

member_experience_collection.title: Co-Founder and CEO
member_experience_collection.description:
PadPiper helps renters find monthly housing and compatible housemates. Moving to a new place for just a few months can be difficult and lonely. PadPiper enables renters to browse furnished rentals, find housemates with similar interests and lifestyles, choose beds, and split deposit and rent payments.

We're on a mission to help people find their home. We believe that home is a collection of people, places, and experiences. We're proud to have already helped over two thousand students find their home during their internships since PadPiper launched in October 2016.

I was in charge of researching, designing, and building two internal applications. Both saved employees hours of their week totaling over $50k in saved expenses for the company. The full process involved requirements analysis for both tools, design, development, and iteration/improvement based on employee feedback.

Accomplishments:
- Built a database configuration tool that enabled engineers to view all database keys used on Zazzle.com, search for specific ones, and add/edit/delete specific key values.
- Built a translation tool that allowed the translation team to view untranslated strings based on a set of filters, export them to Excel, import translated strings, and view translated strings based on a set of filters.
- Presented both tools to the entire company at the end of the internship
- Won Pi Day (recited 30 digits of Pi from memory)

Stack:
- CSS3/SCSS and HTML5
- AngularJS (ES6)
- Angular Material CSS framework
- .NET backend framework
- Restful API integrations
- OOP&D
- SQL database queries
- Git
            

    
    

    
        Show less

member_experience_collection.title: Software Engineer
member_experience_collection.description:
I was incredibly fortunate to be a part of such a well-run agile development team. I was a software engineer, focused on frontend, for the Pulse team, working on online Fifa Ultimate Team content.

Accomplishments:
- One of six agile team members building the first accompanying web app to EA's most profitable game (FIFA)
- Created the entire frontend from scratch with a teammate
- Improved code-coverage (testing) from ~40% to ~95%
- Made it into the credits of FIFA 15!

Stack and process:
- Agile development including 2-week sprints, story-pointing, and scrums
- JIRA
- CSS3/SCSS and HTML5
- AngularJS (ES6) frontend framework
- Cucumber and Selenium frontend testing
- Symfony2 backend framework
- Restful API integrations
- OOP&D
- SQL database queries

member_experience_collection.title: Project Manager
member_experience_collection.description:
Jumping into the world of project management taught me a lot in a short amount of time, from dealing with the politics to tight deadlines. Having experience in both software development and project management has given me a valuable outlook on running a functional and cohesive company.

Accomplishments:
- Saved the company $25k/year by coding multiple Pearl scripts and VB Excel macros to automate control room scheduling (the room responsible for powering all of BC and some of Alberta, Washington, Oregon, and California)
- Created 10-year strategic roadmap for Grid Operations team
- Introduced the company to Prezi 3D presentation software for more effective presentations

member_experience_collection.title: Web Developer
member_experience_collection.description:
Diving into the tech capitol of the world was a phenomenal experience, both inside and outside of work. During this internship I truly fell in love with programming and knew that I wanted to pursue frontend engineering. Fun fact: I put VIM keyboard shortcuts poster next to my desk to become a pro VIM-user.

Accomplishments:
- Increased company revenue 17% by creating an application to organize company products, create social posts/press releases, and view analytics
- Learned proper agile development and programming best practices
- Learned about the hardware Gumstix sold (customizable motherboards)

Stack and process:
- Agile development including 2-week sprints
- VIM
- Vanilla JS with jQuery
- Google APIs
- Git

member_experience_collection.title: Co-Founder
member_experience_collection.description:
My classmate and I started a music recommendation system built around Spotify's Discover Weekly concept years before Discover Weekly was released. We were amongst 15 companies accepted into the University of Waterloo's Enterprise Co-op program. We ultimately didn't stick with the project since school and internships stole our attention.

Accomplishments:
- Learned the fundamentals of programming (with help from my co-founder's father who worked at Microsoft)
- Learned the fundamentals of the web, including HTTP, client/server, HTML/CSS, etc.
- Applied software engineering course knowledge to a real-world application
- Released an Alpha version of the web app

Stack:
- Vanilla Javascript frontend
- .NET backend
- Postgres database

member_recommendations_collection.recommendation: “I had the unique pleasure of working with Jack at Electronic Arts for the duration of his co-op term. He was part of our web development team building a new web application from the ground up using cutting edge markup, CSS and JavaScript. He had never developed with Angular JS prior to the project but I was told he picked it up faster than anyone we'd seen to date. He quickly became an integral and dependable part of our team, showing an enthusiasm for the medium, the project, the tech stack and for getting things done quick. It was a great shame when Jack's co-op term ended, we'd certainly have hired him outright and may do so one day. Hes a great guy to have around and any team should be so lucky to have him on board.”
